quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,82,"No! They [i.e., those "
  19,83,"Do you not see that We have sent the devils upon the disbelievers, inciting them [to evil] with [constant] incitement?"
  19,84,"So be not impatient over them. We only count out [i.e., allow] to them a [limited] number.{1}",1:[Of breaths, of days, or of evil deeds.]
  20,64,"So resolve upon your plan and then come [forward] in line. And he has succeeded today who overcomes."
  20,65,"They said, "
  20,66,"He said, "
  21,40,"Rather, it will come to them unexpectedly and bewilder them, and they will not be able to repel it, nor will they be reprieved."
  21,41,"And already were messengers ridiculed before you, but those who mocked them were enveloped by what they used to ridicule."
  21,42,"Say, "
  22,16,"And thus have We sent it [i.e., the Qur’ān] down as verses of clear evidence and because Allāh guides whom He intends."
  22,17,"Indeed, those who have believed and those who were Jews and the Sabeans and the Christians and the Magians and those who associated with Allāh - Allāh will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection. Indeed Allāh is, over all things, Witness.{1}",1:[See footnote of 4:79.]
  22,18,"Do you not see [i.e., know] that to Allāh prostrates whoever is in the heavens and whoever is on the earth and the sun, the moon, the stars, the mountains, the trees, the moving creatures and many of the people? But upon many the punishment has been justified.{1} And he whom Allāh humiliates - for him there is no bestower of honor. Indeed, Allāh does what He wills.",1:[And therefore decreed.]
